# Version control governance

- **Branches**: Prefer short, prefixed names: `feature/…`, `fix/…`, `chore/…`, `docs/…`. Rebase or merge from the default branch regularly so PRs stay current.
- **Commits**: Use an imperative subject line (e.g. “Add loading state to ChatMessage”). Keep one logical change per commit when practical; use the body for context, trade-offs, or ticket references.
- **Public repository — no secrets, ever.** This repo is public on GitHub. Anything committed becomes world-readable and cannot be un-published by a later deletion (history is preserved on forks and mirrors). Before `git add`, scan your staged content for credentials.
  - **Azure Function key** (the `?code=…` suffix on the backend URL): belongs in the **host page's `<script>` tag** that calls `SiiliChatbot.init({ apiUrl })`, never in this repo.
  - **`VITE_API_URL`** for local development: belongs in **`.env.local`** (already matched by the `*.local` rule in `.gitignore`). Do not hardcode the URL in `src/main.tsx`, `README.md`, or examples — use a `https://YOUR-BACKEND/api/chat` placeholder.
  - **Other credentials** (personal access tokens, service principals, SAS URLs, private CORS origins): never in the repo. Use the host's / CI's secret store.
  - If a secret is committed by accident, treat the secret as compromised: **rotate it first**, then scrub history. Do not rely on `git rm` or a force-push to "hide" it — assume it's already been scraped.
  - External disclosure of a leaked secret: follow [`../../SECURITY.md`](../../SECURITY.md) (`it@siili.com`).
- **Artifacts**: `dist/` and `node_modules/` are ignored—do not force-add build output unless the team explicitly maintains release artifacts in-repo.
- **Shared history**: Avoid force-pushing to the default branch. History rewrites on feature branches only with clear team agreement.
- **Pull requests**: Include a short summary, how you verified the change (e.g. `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, manual steps), and links to issues or acceptance criteria when applicable. Prefer reviewable PR size over mega-diffs.
- **Hooks**: A repo-managed `.husky/pre-commit` hook runs `npx lint-staged` (ESLint `--fix` on staged `.ts` / `.tsx`) followed by `npm run verify` (which runs `npm run build` and enforces the `Automated:` ACs in `ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md`). Husky self-installs via the `prepare` script on `npm install`. The hook is the only gate — there is no CI — so do not skip it silently. `git commit --no-verify` is the documented escape hatch for explicit WIP commits, and per [`change-boundary.mdc`](change-boundary.mdc) it MUST NOT be used unless the user explicitly requests it.
